s breathed at ''Ralawta.'' A cenotaph(''Chhatri'') was built at the place where he died. Recently a statue of Maharao Shekha was also inaugurated at the same place by then-President of India Smt. Pratibha Patil <ref>{{Cite book|last=Sinh|first=Ranbir|title=History Of Shekhawats|publisher=Publication Scheme|year=2001|isbn=8186782745|location=Jaipur|pages=}}</ref> [[File:Innorgration of maharao shekha statue.jpg|thumb|Inauguration of Maharao Shekha statue by Honorable [[President of India]] [[Pratibha Patil]]]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[History of Rajasthan]]\n*[[Rajput]]\n*[[Rajputana]]\n*[[James Tod]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shekha Of Amarsar}}\n[[Category:15th-century Indian monarchs]]\n", "name_user": "Chaitanyasinghshekhawat", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shekha_of_Amarsar"}
